1.  d/dx [ e^{x^{2}} / e^{5x} ]

   Combine the exponentials first:
   e^{x^{2}} / e^{5x} = e^{x^{2}-5x}

   Differentiate:
   d/dx [ e^{x^{2}-5x} ] = e^{x^{2}-5x} · d/dx (x^{2}-5x)
                         = e^{x^{2}-5x} · (2x - 5)

   Answer: (2x – 5) e^{x^{2}-5x}

2.  d/dt [ (e^{2t})^{3} ]

   Rewrite the power:
   (e^{2t})^{3} = e^{6t}

   Differentiate:
   d/dt [ e^{6t} ] = 6 e^{6t}

   (Alternatively, using the chain rule directly:
   3(e^{2t})^{2} · d/dt(e^{2t}) = 3e^{4t} · 2e^{2t} = 6e^{6t}.)

   Answer: 6 e^{6t}
